  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001_1",
    "text": "Larisa Brown Defence Editor",
    "canon_role": "section_header",
    "bbox": [
      0.03707823507601038,
      0.28134556574923547,
      0.16240266963292546,
      0.290665501674676
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001",
    "order": 6
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001_2",
    "text": "Defence companies have stopped attending university careers fairs and events because of security fears over protesters, affecting recruitment at a time of heightened global threats.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.034853540971449756,
      0.2964904616280763,
      0.21208750463477938,
      0.34076015727391873
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001",
    "order": 7
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001_7",
    "text": "In recent months, some 20 defence companies are believed to have been advised against attending careers fairs and university events because of security and safety fears, or decided to cancel them amid pressure, according to Kevin Craven, chief executive of the ADS group, which represents defence, aerospace and security companies. Those that did attend faced intimida- tion and harassment, he said.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.41305153874675565,
      0.2976554536187564,
      0.5902855024100853,
      0.36813746905490025
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001",
    "order": 8
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001_9",
    "text": "Leonardo UK, a defence firm that supplies equipment to the MoD, accused some universities of \"self-censoring\" which its chief executive warned could affect Britain's security.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.6028921023359288,
      0.3058103975535168,
      0.778642936596218,
      0.34949759720401924
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001",
    "order": 9
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001_13",
    "text": "\"Activism against defence organisa- tions has always been present, but the level of destruction we're now seeing is concerning primarily for our people,\" one industry source said.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.7927326659251019,
      0.30639289354885685,
      0.967741935483871,
      0.35008009319935923
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001",
    "order": 10
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001_5",
    "text": "Employees of some firms, including younger members of staff acting as Stem (science, technology, engineering and maths) ambassadors, have been intimidated and harassed by protesters when on campuses, insiders claimed.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.22543566926214312,
      0.33260521333915827,
      0.40044493882091214,
      0.3675549730595602
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001",
    "order": 11
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001_3",
    "text": "Firms making weapons for the Ministry of Defence and for export have been effectively excluded from attending events on campus at some universities, or forced to cancel them themselves, raising concerns that national security could be put at risk as a result of a skills shortage in vital industries.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.036336670374490176,
      0.3413426532692588,
      0.21134593993325917,
      0.3675549730595602
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001",
    "order": 12
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001_10",
    "text": "Industry sources said there had been greater hostility since the Israel-Gaza war began in October 2023, and com- panies had been investing tens of thou- sands of pounds to protect their staff.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.6051167964404894,
      0.35008009319935923,
      0.7779013718946978,
      0.3675549730595602
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001",
    "order": 13
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001_14",
    "text": "Amid growing concern at the scale of Continued on page 2",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.7934742306266221,
      0.35008009319935923,
      0.9670003707823508,
      0.3675549730595602
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001",
    "order": 14
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001_15",
    "text": "Schools bill 'is an act of vandalism', blast Tories",
    "canon_role": "section_header",
    "bbox": [
      0.7912495365220615,
      0.38211737294306103,
      0.939562476826103,
      0.48696665210426676
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001",
    "order": 15
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001_11",
    "text": "",
    "canon_role": "picture",
    "bbox": [
      0.035595105672969966,
      0.3838648609290811,
      0.7779013718946978,
      0.6803553225571575
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001",
    "order": 16
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001_16",
    "text": "Nicola Woolcock Education Editor Oliver Wright Policy Editor",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.7934742306266221,
      0.5003640599970876,
      0.9432703003337041,
      0.5190039318479686
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001",
    "order": 17
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001_17",
    "text": "The new schools bill is \"pure vandal- ism\" that will rip up academy freedoms that have resulted in excellence and lead to micromanagement, the Conservatives have said.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.7912495365220615,
      0.5242463958060288,
      0.967741935483871,
      0.5685160914518713
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001",
    "order": 18
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001_18",
    "text": "All schools will have to follow the national curriculum under the new Children's Wellbeing and Schools Bill, which has its second reading today. The government says the bill will protect vulnerable children by creating a home education register and unique identify- ing number, to make it easier to protect pupils who disappear from the system.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.7912495365220615,
      0.5690985874472113,
      0.967741935483871,
      0.6477355468181156
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001",
    "order": 19
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001_20",
    "text": "However, academy heads say the changes, which could also impose national pay scales on all state schools, would threaten their ability to attract good staff.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.7912495365220615,
      0.6477355468181156,
      0.967741935483871,
      0.691422746468618
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001",
    "order": 20
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001_21",
    "text": "More than half of all schools are now academies — state schools currently free from local authority control. The movement began under Tony Blair's government but was expanded widely under Michael Gove.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.7919911012235817,
      0.691422746468618,
      0.967741935483871,
      0.743847386049221
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001",
    "order": 21
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001_19",
    "text": "Patients to face two-day waits at A&E in flu crisis",
    "canon_role": "section_header",
    "bbox": [
      0.036336670374490176,
      0.7054026503567788,
      0.7727104189840563,
      0.8160768894713849
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001",
    "order": 22
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001_22",
    "text": "Forcing all schools including acade- mies to follow the national curriculum, which is undergoing a review led by Professor Becky Francis, would jeopar- dise standards, the Tories claim.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.7919911012235817,
      0.744429882044561,
      0.967741935483871,
      0.7875345856997233
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001",
    "order": 23
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001_24",
    "text": "Neil O'Brien, the shadow schools minister, said the bill was \"one of the most dumb and tragic things I can re- member. It's an act of pure vandalism, abolishing academies in all but name.\"",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.7919911012235817,
      0.7875345856997233,
      0.9684835001853912,
      0.8318042813455657
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001",
    "order": 24
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001_23",
    "text": "Health secretary admits 'shame' as doctors warn of unsafe care",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.03707823507601038,
      0.8219018494247852,
      0.5124212087504635,
      0.8382117372943061
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001",
    "order": 25
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001_38",
    "text": "He added: \"Instead of paying more to hire and retain good teachers, the land- scape will be squashed flat.' The best and those who do more will get paid the same as the average, and more of the best teachers will leave the profession.\"",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.7919911012235817,
      0.8323867773409058,
      0.967741935483871,
      0.8842289209261687
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001",
    "order": 26
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001_29",
    "text": "",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.22543566926214312,
      0.8486966652104266,
      0.40044493882091214,
      0.8842289209261687
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001",
    "order": 27
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001_35",
    "text": "",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.6021505376344086,
      0.8486966652104266,
      0.7793845012977382,
      0.8929663608562691
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001",
    "order": 28
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001_32",
    "text": "",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.41305153874675565,
      0.8492791612057667,
      0.5895439377085651,
      0.9022862967817096
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001",
    "order": 29
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001_25",
    "text": "Poppy Koronka Health Correspondent",
    "canon_role": "section_header",
    "bbox": [
      0.036336670374490176,
      0.8510266491917868,
      0.20689655172413793,
      0.8609290811125674
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001",
    "order": 30
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001_26",
    "text": "Patients have been warned of two-day waits in A&E as nine hospitals around the country declared critical incidents and the NHS struggled to cope with the winter flu crisis.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.034853540971449756,
      0.8661715450706277,
      0.21134593993325917,
      0.91044124071647
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001",
    "order": 31
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001_30",
    "text": "NHS bosses said flu cases had \"sky- rocketed\"_to about 5,000 a day, and Sir Keir Starmer is facing questions about his decision to prioritise routine operations in a week when A&E units are struggling to cope.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.2239525398591027,
      0.8842289209261687,
      0.40118650352243235,
      0.9372360565021115
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001",
    "order": 32
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001_39",
    "text": "Schools would no longer be allowed to employ teachers without qualified teacher status. This would affect about 13,600 existing staff, more than twice as many as the 6,500 that the government has said it will recruit, he said.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.7919911012235817,
      0.8842289209261687,
      0.967741935483871,
      0.9366535605067715
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001",
    "order": 33
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001_36",
    "text": "Flu appears to be particularly bad this year, with the latest data showing that cases were nearly 3.5 times higher than the same week last year. However, others pointed out that the number of flu cases was similar two years ago.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.6028921023359288,
      0.8935488568516091,
      0.7793845012977382,
      0.9459734964322121
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001",
    "order": 34
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001_33",
    "text": "RSV, respiratory syncytial virus, has symptoms similar to the common cold but can lead to more serious lung conditions and breathing problems.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.41527623285131626,
      0.9022862967817096,
      0.5895439377085651,
      0.9372360565021115
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001",
    "order": 35
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001_27",
    "text": "Senior doctors warned of \"unsafe and unacceptable care\" that was likely to cost lives, while hospitals blamed exceptionally high demand at the busiest time of year.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.034853540971449756,
      0.9110237367118101,
      0.21134593993325917,
      0.9547109363623125
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001",
    "order": 36
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001_40",
    "text": "O'Brien added: \"The freedom to vary from the national curriculum promotes genuine diversity in our schools. Not all Continued on page 8",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.7912495365220615,
      0.9372360565021115,
      0.9684835001853912,
      0.9721858162225134
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001",
    "order": 37
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001_31",
    "text": "Nine hospitals across five trusts in England have declared critical incidents in the past week, with all referencing flu, infectious diseases or winter pressures as contributing fac- tors. Professor Sir Stephen Powis, the national medical director for NHS England, cited a \"quad-demic\" of illness as outbreaks of flu, Covid, norovirus and RSV add to pressure on hospitals.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.22543566926214312,
      0.9378185524974516,
      0.40044493882091214,
      0.9727683122178535
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001",
    "order": 38
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001_34",
    "text": "\"Frontline NHS staff are under significant pressure and the demand is showing no signs of letting up, with latest data showing flu cases sky- rocketed to around 5,000 a day in hos- pitals at the end of last year and multi- ple trusts across the country declaring incidents to help them to manage addi- tional strain on services,\" Powis said.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.41453466814979606,
      0.9378185524974516,
      0.5895439377085651,
      0.9727683122178535
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001",
    "order": 39
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001_37",
    "text": "Adrian Boyle, the president of the Royal College of Emergency Medicine, Continued on page 2",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.6028921023359288,
      0.9465559924275521,
      0.7801260659992585,
      0.9721858162225134
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001",
    "order": 40
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001_28",
    "text": "Wes Streeting, the health secretary, said he was \"ashamed\" of the plight of patients languishing in corridors but warned that significant improvements in care would not happen until next winter.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.036336670374490176,
      0.9547109363623125,
      0.21134593993325917,
      0.9727683122178535
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Times UK_0801@magazinesclubnew_page_001",
    "order": 41
  }
]